## SharePoint Online portal update

We are preparing to move our current SharePoint portal to a new SharePoint Online portal. Many business areas have already moved to SharePoint Online, and we already use Microsoft 365 tools such as Outlook, Teams and OneDrive, so moving the portal to SharePoint Online is a natural next step and supports the company’s broader move to modern, cloud-based services.

For most users, the portal will feel familiar. The new SharePoint Online portal will follow a similar structure to the current site, with an updated design and the benefits that come with the cloud platform. This is not intended to be a major change to how people use the portal day to day.

The move is planned to take place from Friday 26 July and is expected to be completed by Monday morning. During this time, the SharePoint portal may be unavailable for short periods while the migration work is completed. Further details will be shared closer to the date if any user action is required.
